<title type="html"><![CDATA[Original Apple II Prince of Persia's source code released]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8830&amp;p=92637#p92637"><![CDATA[
Re: fluidity of motion in original PoP: I forget where I read this (probably an Apple II magazine like BYTE or similar), but I believe the fluidity stems from Jordan Mechner's desire to provide very smooth animations for his bitmaps (e.g. single-pixel changes, thus lots of frames).<br /><br />This stems from an earlier game Justin worked on/wrote, called Karateka, where to get the animations looking accurate and smooth -- and this is what I remember reading specifically -- he travelled and actually watched martial artists practise/spar.  I'm certain he took that same knowledge and applied it to PoP.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Thu Apr 19, 2012 11:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
