<title type="html"><![CDATA[Original Apple II Prince of Persia's source code released]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8830&amp;p=92630#p92630"><![CDATA[
For all of you ASM coder out there, you might be happy to hear the the original Apple II source code for Prince of Persia was released a few days ago. The author believed the source to be lost for decades before catching a lucky break and finding some 3.5'' floppy in an old box. You can read about this interesting story at <a href="http://jordanmechner.com/blog/2012/04/source/" class="postlink">http://jordanmechner.com/blog/2012/04/source/</a> and download the source from github. There's also documentation available explaining some part of it. I am no programmer but I am sure this would be something fun to check out if I knew any ASM. Now I'm hoping someone will get cracking on a Vectrex port <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4859">SkinnyV</a> — Thu Apr 19, 2012 4:10 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
